To find (A△B)△C, we first need to find A△B, which is the symmetric difference between sets A and B. The symmetric difference is the set of elements which are in either of the sets, but not in their intersection.

A = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
B = {2, 4, 6, 8, 10}

Intersection of A and B: A ∩ B = {2, 4}
A△B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B) = {1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10}

Now we need to find the symmetric difference between (A△B) and C:

(A△B) = {1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10}
C = {1, 3, 5, 7, 9}

Intersection of (A△B) and C: (A△B) ∩ C = {1, 3, 5}
(A△B)△C = ((A△B) ∪ C) - ((A△B) ∩ C) = {6, 7, 8, 9, 10}

So, (A△B)△C = {6, 7, 8, 9, 10}.
